HEADWORD: Protomartyr
<hw>Pro"to*mar`tyr</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL., fr. Gr.
<?/; <?/ first + <?/ martyr: cf. F. <ets>protomartyr</ets>. See
<er>Proto-</er>, and <er>Martyr</er>.]</ety> <def>The first martyr; the
first who suffers, or is sacrificed, in any cause; -- applied esp. to
Stephen, the first Christian martyr.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

